      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JUKEBOX DUKE (4) was prominent throughout when winning in one of the fastest times of the card two back but could manage only midfield last time when finished 4th and beaten 9 lengths at Gawler (22.90). Has good box speed and can overcome the tricky draw. Worth another chance. BLUE PRIDE (6) had been in super honest form hitting the frame two times on end before finishing sixth (17.35) at Murray Bridge last time. Solid record at the distance winning four races. Should be in this for a long way. MY MUM'S VALUE (8) was never in contention last time after settling well back at Murray Bridge, but prior to that won by a neck at this track (17.30) beating BLUE PRIDE in a Invitation on March 10. Has good speed and will be prominent from out wide. Should be about the money. DAYNE'S CALAIS (2) is always hard to beat when he races at this trip.",
